        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="422"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <head>422. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD3"
                        type="to">Rusk</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d422fn0">Source: <persName corresp="#p_KJF2"
                            >Kennedy</persName> Library, National Security Files, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BWH2">Brubeck</persName> Series, South Africa.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-11-07">November 7, 1963</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I agree with your proposed course of action on South Africa in the Security
                    Council and share strongly your view that, having made a major concession in
                    August, we cannot get in the position of having to make substantial new
                    concessions on this issue every few months. I think it important, therefore,
                    that in announcing our willingness to apply the arms embargo to “materials for
                    the production of military equipment” we make it very clear that we regard this
                    as merely part of the position we voluntarily took in August and that the August
                    resolution should be given a more reasonable further term to do its work.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d422fn1">Printed from an unsigned copy that indicates the
                        President signed the original.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
